\\n@@ -77,3 +77,29 @@ The GUI must treat the runner as the normal execution path for local file-writin\\n 5. Warn visibly that free terminal shortcuts are not the normal path.\\n \\n The GUI is not the safety anchor. The safety anchors remain `agentic-kit`, path validation, hash validation, tests, Git, PR CI, protected-change planning, and repo-backed evidence.\\n+\\n+## Secure remote connector Branch/PR/Merge path\\n+\\n+When the ChatGPT GitHub connector is available, it may be used to create or update UTF-8 text files in the repository, but the safe repository mutation path is still governed by `agentic-kit` wrappers. Raw `git`/`gh` commands are not the normal operator interface for this path.\\n+\\n+Required route for connector-backed repository updates:\\n+\\n+1. Create and push a feature branch with `agentic-kit transfer branch-create <branch> --push`.\\n+2. Switch to that branch with `agentic-kit transfer branch-switch <branch> --pull`.\\n+3. Use the GitHub connector only for direct-path file create/update operations on that feature branch.\\n+4. Pull the feature branch locally with `agentic-kit transfer pull-current`.\\n+5. Run the relevant local gates before PR creation.\\n+6. Create the pull request with `agentic-kit transfer pr-create --head <branch> --base main`.\\n+7. Inspect the PR with `agentic-kit transfer pr-status <pr> --expected-head-sha <full_sha>`.\\n+8. Wait for CI with `agentic-kit transfer pr-wait-ci <pr> --expected-head-sha <full_sha>`.\\n+9. Merge only with `agentic-kit transfer pr-merge-safe <pr> --expected-head-sha <full_sha>`.\\n+10. After merge, run the post-merge handoff freshness check and refresh handoff state if required.\\n+\\n+Safety requirements:\\n+\\n+- The connector must not write directly to `main` for product work.\\n+- The connector must not replace protected governance, YAML, status, or handoff files wholesale.\\n+- The PR head SHA must be treated as a pinned merge precondition.\\n+- Merge readiness is not inferred from visual inspection, small diffs, or \\u201cgreen-looking\\u201d UI state.\\n+- A dirty worktree blocks the route until the dirty paths are reviewed, committed intentionally, or cleaned.\\n+- If connector access is unavailable or insufficient, the fallback must be named explicitly in the evidence log.\\n\"\n+}\n+\n+### VERIFY REQUIRED CONTENT EXISTS IN WORKTREE ###\n+MISSING_TERM tests/test_secure_remote_connector_branch_pr_merge_path.py: test_secure_remote_connector_branch_pr_merge_path_is_documented\n+\n+### LOCAL GATES ###\n+Agentic project check passed\n+Documentation mesh audit\n+\n+Documents:\n+- README.md: current-state, required\n+- CHANGELOG.md: release-history, required\n+- docs/releases/VERIFIED_RELEASES.md: release-history, optional\n+- CITATION.cff: current-state, required\n+- pyproject.toml: current-state, required\n+- src/agentic_project_kit/__init__.py: current-state, required\n+- docs/STATUS.md: current-state, required\n+- docs/handoff/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md: current-state, required\n+- AGENTS.md: governance, required\n+- docs/TEST_GATES.md: governance, required\n+- docs/DOCUMENTATION_COVERAGE.yaml: governance, required\n+- sentinel.yaml: governance, required\n+- .agentic/project.yaml: governance, required\n+- docs/architecture/ARCHITECTURE_CONTRACT.md: architecture, required\n+- docs/architecture/DOCUMENTATION_INFORMATION_ARCHITECTURE.md: architecture, required\n+- docs/WORKFLOW_OUTPUT_CYCLE.md: architecture, required\n+- DESIGN.md: architecture, optional\n+- docs/reports/status_roadmap_summary_after_pr105_20260512.md: historical-plan, required\n+- docs/V0.3.0_OUTPUT_REPAIR_PLAN.md: historical-plan, optional\n+\n+Documentation registry:\n+- registry: docs/DOCUMENTATION_REGISTRY.yaml\n+- version: 1\n+- documents: 22\n+- broad_migration_allowed: False\n+- class:architecture: 1\n+- class:evidence/log: 2\n+- class:generated artifact: 1\n+- class:governance/system: 4\n+- class:operational/automation: 4\n+- class:planning: 7\n+- class:release: 2\n+- class:user-fa